\section{Entry vectors}

The file loads at [[$0800]] and is entered at its first byte by the
library's \textsc{brun}. The second vector replays the animation
without re-running \texttt{MAKE.INDATA} (the attract loop uses it),
and the third is a no-op hook.

<<u1intro entry vectors>>=
        ORG $0800
INTRO_ENTRY
        JMP INTRO_COLD
INTRO_REPLAY_VEC
        JMP INTRO_REPLAY
        RTS                             ; spare no-op vector
@ %def INTRO_ENTRY INTRO_REPLAY_VEC

\section{Hi-res line address tables}

Lookup tables for the base address of each of the 192 hi-res screen
lines (page 1, [[HGR1]]); every drawing routine indexes these by line
number instead of computing the interleaved address. Adding [[$70]] to
a high byte retargets the same line in the [[HGR_SAVE]] copy at
[[$9000]]; adding [[$20]] retargets page 2.

<<hires line tables>>=
        ORG $0807
HGR_LINE_LO
        HEX 00 00 00 00 00 00 00 00
        HEX 80 80 80 80 80 80 80 80
        HEX 00 00 00 00 00 00 00 00
        HEX 80 80 80 80 80 80 80 80
        HEX 00 00 00 00 00 00 00 00
        HEX 80 80 80 80 80 80 80 80
