<<twn drop>>=
        ORG $8CBE
CMD_DROP
        SUBROUTINE
        ; The Drop command front end: Pence, Weapon, or Armour.
        ;
        ; Behavior:
        ;   Read one of P/W/A, echo the matching prompt from DROP_PROMPTS,
        ;   and RTS-dispatch through DROP_DISP to the chosen sub-handler.
        JSR MSG_PRINT
        DC.B " Pence,Weapon,Armour: ",0
        JSR KEY_IDLE
        LDX #$06
        STX MON_CH
        LDX #$03
.L8CE1
        CMP $8CFE,X
        BEQ .L8CE9
        DEX
        BNE .L8CE1
.L8CE9
        TXA
        ASL
        TAY
        LDA DROP_DISP+1,Y
        PHA
        LDA DROP_DISP,Y
        PHA
        JSR STR_NTH
        DC.W DROP_PROMPTS
        JSR CLR_EOL
        INC MON_CH
        RTS
@

The Drop front end matches the typed letter against the three-byte
selector ``PWA'' and RTS-dispatches through [[DROP_DISP]], a table of
\emph{return addresses} (target $-1$) pushed onto the stack.

<<twn drop dispatch>>=
        ORG $8CFF
DROP_SEL
        DC.B "PWA"               ; Drop sub-command letters
DROP_DISP ; RTS-dispatch (target-1), indexed by 2*letter:
        DC.W DROP_SEL-2          ;   Y=0 slot (unused)
        DC.W DROP_PENCE-1        ;   P: drop gold
        DC.W DROP_WEAPON-1       ;   W: drop a weapon
        DC.W DROP_ARMOUR-1       ;   A: drop armour
@

<<twn drop pence>>=
        ORG $8D0A
DROP_PENCE
        SUBROUTINE
        ; Drop Pence: give gold to the person on the player tile.
        ;
        ; Behavior:
        ;   Read an amount (NUM_INPUT), deduct it from PLR_COIN.  If the
        ;   tile holds the special benefactor NPC (type $61 from NPC_AT),
        ;   the gift returns 1.5x its value as hit points and a random
        ;   spell ("Shazam!" / "Alakazot!"); otherwise just "Ok!".
        JSR MSG_PRINT
        DC.B "~How much? ",0
        JSR NUM_INPUT
        LDA AMOUNT
        ORA AMOUNT+1
        BNE .L8D25
        RTS
.L8D25
        LDA PLR_COIN
        CMP AMOUNT
        LDA PLR_COIN+1
        SBC AMOUNT+1
        BCS .L8D53
        JSR MSG_PRINT
        DC.B "~Thou hast not that much!",0
        JMP BEEP_HUH
.L8D53
        LDA PLR_COIN
        SEC
        SBC AMOUNT
        STA PLR_COIN
        LDA PLR_COIN+1
        SBC AMOUNT+1
        STA PLR_COIN+1
        LDX ZP_X
        LDY ZP_Y
        JSR NPC_AT
        CMP #$61
        BEQ .L8D7A
        JSR MSG_PRINT
        DC.B "~Ok!",0
        RTS
.L8D7A
        LDA AMOUNT
        STA ZP_T0
        LDA AMOUNT+1
        LSR
        STA ZP_T1
        ROR ZP_T0
        LDA ZP_T0
        CLC
        ADC AMOUNT
        STA ZP_T0
        LDA ZP_T1
        ADC AMOUNT+1
        STA ZP_T1
        LDA PLR_HITS
        CLC
        ADC ZP_T0
        STA PLR_HITS
        LDA PLR_HITS+1
        ADC ZP_T1
        STA PLR_HITS+1
        LDA PLR_HITS
        CMP #$0F
        LDA PLR_HITS+1
        SBC #$27
        BCC .L8DBD
        LDA #$0F
        STA PLR_HITS
        LDA #$27
        STA PLR_HITS+1
.L8DBD
        JSR RND
        CMP #$10
        BCC .L8DD5
        JSR MSG_PRINT
        DC.B "~Shazam!",0
        LDA #$0A
        JMP SFX_PLAY
.L8DD5
        JSR RND
        AND #$0F
        CMP #$08
        BCS .L8DD5
        CMP #$03
        BEQ .L8DD5
        TAX
        INX
        INC OWNED_SPELLS,X
        JSR MSG_PRINT
        DC.B "~Alakazot!",0
        LDA #$0A
        JMP SFX_PLAY
DROP_WEAPON
        JSR DROP_PICK
        DC.B $0F
        DC.B $83
        ROR STR_WEAPONS,X
        BMI .L8E12
        TAX
        LDA #$00
        STA OWNED_WEAPONS,X
        CPX READY_WEAPON
        BNE .L8E12
        STA READY_WEAPON
.L8E12
        JMP MAP_DRAW
DROP_ARMOUR
        JSR DROP_PICK
        ORA $7D
        ROR STR_ARMOUR,X
        BMI .L8E12
        TAX
        LDA #$00
        STA OWNED_ARMOUR,X
        CPX READY_ARMOUR
        BNE .L8E12
        STA READY_ARMOUR
        JMP MAP_DRAW
CAP_FOOD
        LDA PLR_FOOD
        CMP #$0F
        LDA PLR_FOOD+1
        SBC #$27
        BCC .L8E46
        LDA #$0F
        STA PLR_FOOD
        LDA #$27
        STA PLR_FOOD+1
.L8E46
        RTS
CAP_COIN
        LDA PLR_COIN
        CMP #$0F
        LDA PLR_COIN+1
        SBC #$27
        BCC .L8E5D
        LDA #$0F
        STA PLR_COIN
        LDA #$27
        STA PLR_COIN+1
.L8E5D
        RTS
@

[[DROP_PROMPTS]] is the packed sub-prompt table echoed by Drop:
\emph{nothing}, \emph{pence}, \emph{weapon:}, \emph{armour:}.

<<twn drop prompts>>=
        ORG $8E5E
DROP_PROMPTS
        HEX 6e6f7468696ee770
        HEX 656e63e577656170
        HEX 6f6eba61726d6f75
        HEX 72ba
@

<<twn drop pick>>=
        ORG $8E78
DROP_PICK
        SUBROUTINE
        ; DROP_PICK: a popup item picker that takes five inline argument
        ; bytes after the JSR (count, owned-array pointer lo/hi, name-table
        ; pointer lo/hi), pulled off the stack like the engine MENU_PICK.
        ;
        ; Behavior:
        ;   List the owned items as a)..  in a popup, wait for a letter,
        ;   and return its index in X (or X=$FF for none).  CMD_GET, Quit,
        ;   Ready follow.
        PLA
        STA MSG_PTR
        PLA
        STA MSG_PTR+1
        JSR MSG_GETC
        STA PICK_CNT
        JSR MSG_GETC
        STA ZP_PICK_PTR
        JSR MSG_GETC
        STA ZP_PICK_PTR+1
        JSR MSG_GETC
        STA PICK_TBL
        JSR MSG_GETC
        STA PICK_TBL+1
        LDA MSG_PTR+1
        PHA
        LDA MSG_PTR
        PHA
        LDY PICK_CNT
        LDX #$00
.L8EA9
        LDA (ZP_PICK_PTR),Y
        BEQ .L8EAE
        INX
.L8EAE
        DEY
        BNE .L8EA9
        STX ZP_PICK_CNT
        CPX #$00
        BNE .L8EBC
        PLA
        PLA
        JMP .L8F27
.L8EBC
        JSR WIN_SAVE
        JSR WIN_VIEW
        LDX #$0F
        LDY #$00
        JSR MSG_AT
        DC.B $0E," Drop ",$18,0
        JSR CLR_WINDOW
        SEC
        LDA #$14
        SBC ZP_PICK_CNT
        LSR
        STA MON_CV
        LDA #$61
        STA PICK_ALPHA
        LDY #$00
        BEQ .L8EFA
.L8EE6
        TYA
        PHA
        LDA #$0D
        STA MON_CH
        JSR MSG_PRINT
        DC.B "a) ",0
        PLA
        JSR .L8F35
        TAY
        INC MON_CV
.L8EFA
        CPY PICK_CNT
        BCS .L8F09
        INC PICK_ALPHA
        INY
        LDA (ZP_PICK_PTR),Y
        BNE .L8EE6
        BEQ .L8EFA
.L8F09
        JSR WIN_RESTORE
        JSR KEY_WAIT
        PHA
        JSR POPUP_CLOSE
        SEC
        PLA
        SBC #$41
        BEQ .L8F27
        BMI .L8F27
        CMP PICK_CNT
        BCC .L8F22
        BNE .L8F27
.L8F22
        TAY
        LDA (ZP_PICK_PTR),Y
        BNE .L8F34
.L8F27
        LDY #$FF
        JSR MSG_PRINT
        DC.B "none",0
        TYA
        TAX
        RTS
.L8F34
        TYA
.L8F35
        TAX
        PHA
PICK_TBL = *+3
        JSR STR_NTH_CAP
        DC.W ZP_X
        PLA
        RTS
        ASL
CMD_GET
        JSR MSG_PRINT
        DC.B " what",0
        JMP QUERY_MARK
@

Quit is disabled in town (``only allowed outdoors''); Ready forwards
to the engine [[READY_CMD]] then redraws. [[CMD_GET]] and
[[CMD_UNLOCK]] are the `` what'' + [[QUERY_MARK]] stubs.

<<twn quit ready>>=
        ORG $8F4B
CMD_QUIT
        SUBROUTINE
        ; Quit (and Ready): Quit is refused in town -- saving is only
        ; allowed outdoors -- so it just prints the refusal.  Ready
        ; reads S/W/A and forwards to the engine READY_CMD, then
        ; redraws the town.
        ;
        ; Behavior:
        ;   Quit -> BEEP_HUH after the message; Ready -> READY_CMD.
        LDA #$12
        STA MON_CH
        JSR MSG_PRINT
        DC.B " is~only allowed outdoors!",0
        JMP BEEP_HUH
CMD_READY
        JSR KEY_IDLE
        CMP #$53
        BEQ .L8F80
        CMP #$57
        BEQ .L8F80
        CMP #$41
        BEQ .L8F80
        RTS
.L8F80
        JSR READY_CMD
        JMP MAP_DRAW
@

<<twn steal>>=
        ORG $8F86
CMD_STEAL
        SUBROUTINE
        ; The Steal command: shoplift from a counter NPC.
        ;
        ; Behavior:
        ;   Only the three shop NPCs ($65/$67/$69) can be robbed.  Success
        ;   is automatic for a thief (PLR_CLASS 4), else a roll gated on
        ;   not-yet-caught (AGGRO).  Caught sets AGGRO -- after which no
        ;   shop will trade.  A clean steal yields a random armour piece,
        ;   bags of food, or a weapon depending on the counter.
        LDX ZP_X
        LDY ZP_Y
        JSR NPC_AT
        CMP #$65
        BEQ .L8FAD
        CMP #$67
        BEQ .L8FAD
        CMP #$69
        BEQ .L8FAD
        JSR MSG_PRINT
        DC.B "~Nothing here",0
        JMP QUERY_MARK
