\subsection{Attack}

[[CMD_ATTACK]] is the castle's combat command. It refuses unless a
melee weapon is readied (the same weapon-class test \texttt{TWN}
uses), reads a direction, and marches up to [[WEAPON_HITKIND]] cells
along it ([[ATK_CNT]]) looking for an NPC --- a cell whose glyph is
in the [[$30]]--[[$35]] range. A hit rolls against agility to
connect ([[PLR_AGI]]) and then damage from strength and weapon
([[PLR_STR]]), subtracts it from the NPC's 16-bit hit points in
[[NPC_HP]], and on death frees the slot and awards experience
through [[AWARD_EXP]] (clamped at 9999). Striking a guard (kind~4)
may make him drop a key: [[KEY_KIND]] becomes 1 (silver) or 2 (gold)
on a coin flip, which [[CMD_UNLOCK]] later checks against the
storeroom door. Any swing sets [[KING_REJECT]], so an attacker
forfeits his next royal audience.

<<cas attack>>=
