\subsection{Drop}

[[CMD_DROP]] offers ``Pence, Weapon, Armour''. It matches the key
against [[DROP_KEYS]] and jumps through the RTS-style address table
[[DROP_JMP]] to the chosen sub-handler, echoing the word's name from
[[DROP_STRINGS]]. Dropping pence onto a castle NPC is the same
spell-or-coin transaction \texttt{TWN} uses; dropping a weapon or
armour discards an inventory item through the shared picker
[[DROP_PICK]].

<<cas drop>>=
        ORG $8E5B
CMD_DROP
        SUBROUTINE
        ; Drop: choose Pence, Weapon, or Armour, then dispatch.
        ;
        ; Behavior:
        ;   Read a key, match it against DROP_KEYS, and RTS-jump through
        ;   DROP_JMP to DROP_PENCE / DROP_WEAPON / DROP_ARMOUR.  The chosen
        ;   word's name is echoed from DROP_STRINGS.
        ;
        ; Clobbers: A, X, Y
        JSR MSG_PRINT
        DC.B " Pence,Weapon,Armour: ",0
        JSR KEY_IDLE
        LDX #$06
        STX MON_CH
        LDX #$03
.L8E7E
        CMP DROP_KEYS,X
        BEQ .L8E86
        DEX
        BNE .L8E7E
.L8E86
        TXA
        ASL
        TAY
        LDA DROP_JMP+1,Y
        PHA
        LDA DROP_JMP,Y
        PHA
        JSR STR_NTH
        DC.W DROP_STRINGS
        JSR CLR_EOL
        INC MON_CH
@

[[DROP_KEYS]] holds the three accepted keys (P/W/A) preceded by a
sentinel; [[DROP_JMP]] holds the matching handler addresses minus one,
ready to be pushed and reached by [[RTS]].

<<cas drop dispatch>>=
        ORG $8E9B
DROP_KEYS
        HEX 60505741
DROP_JMP
        HEX 9a8ea68ea58fc08f
@

\subsection{Drop pence, weapon, armour}

[[DROP_PENCE]] reads an amount with [[NUM_INPUT]], debits the coin
purse, and --- if the player faces a receptive NPC (kinds [[$61]]
through [[$63]]) --- gives a gift back: a stat boost, a random spell
through [[OWNED_SPELLS]], or a weapon, scaling with the donation. The
food cap [[CAP_FOOD]] keeps [[PLR_FOOD]] at or below 9999. The two
inventory drops [[DROP_WEAPON]] and [[DROP_ARMOUR]] call [[DROP_PICK]]
with the owned-array and name-table pointers, zero the chosen slot,
un-ready it if it was readied, and redraw the map (the two share
their tail).

<<cas drop pence>>=
        ORG $8EA7
DROP_PENCE
        SUBROUTINE
        ; Drop pence onto an NPC (or DROP_WEAPON/DROP_ARMOUR discards).
        ;
        ; Behavior:
        ;   DROP_PENCE: read an amount, debit PLR_COIN, and if the player
        ;   faces an NPC of kind $61..$63, reward HP, a random spell, or a
        ;   weapon (the gift scales with the amount).  CAP_FOOD clamps food
        ;   at 9999.  DROP_WEAPON / DROP_ARMOUR discard a picked item and
        ;   redraw.
        ;
        ; Clobbers: A, X, Y
        JSR MSG_PRINT
        DC.B "~How much? ",0
        JSR NUM_INPUT
