\subsection{The King's audience}

[[CMD_TRANSACT]] --- the Transact command --- is the heart of the
castle. The player must face the King (NPC kind [[$6C]]) and carry no
grudge ([[KING_REJECT]] must be clear; attacking or being caught
stealing closes the court). The King's response depends on this
castle's slot in [[QUEST_FLAGS]], indexed by [[CASTLE_IDX]]:

\begin{itemize}
\item If the flag's high bit is set, the player has \emph{finished}
  the assigned quest and returned: jump to [[QUEST_COMPLETE]].
\item Otherwise the King asks ``pence or service''. Choosing pence
  runs [[KING_PENCE]]; choosing service runs [[QUEST_ASSIGN]].
\end{itemize}

[[KING_PENCE]] is a donation for hit points: the player names an
amount, it is debited from [[PLR_COIN]], and the King returns it as
hit points at one-and-a-half times the gold (the half is computed by
a shift), capped at 9999.

<<cas transact>>=
        ORG $927C
