\subsection{Quest completion and the rewards}

When the player returns having marked the quest done, the audience
jumps to [[QUEST_COMPLETE]]. It clears the castle's [[QUEST_FLAGS]]
slot, greets the player by name ([[PRINT_NAME]]), and rewards by
parity. An even castle grants strength: $(\$63 - s)/8$ points (where
$s$ is the current [[PLR_STR]], at least one point) toward the maximum
of 99. An odd castle runs
[[QUEST_REWARD_HINT]], which selects one of four per-continent
prophecies through [[GEM_HINT_TBL]] (a self-modified [[JSR]]) --- and
each prophecy comes with one of the four quest gems.

<<cas quest complete>>=
        ORG $94E7
QUEST_COMPLETE
        SUBROUTINE
        ; Complete a quest: clear the flag and reward by parity.
        ;
        ; Behavior:
        ;   Clear this castle's QUEST_FLAGS slot.  EVEN castle: award
        ;   strength points ((99-STR)/8, at least one) toward 99.  ODD
        ;   castle: QUEST_REWARD_HINT -- a per-continent prophecy that also
        ;   grants a quest gem.
        ;
        ; Clobbers: A, X, Y
        JSR POPUP_FRAME
        LDX CASTLE_IDX
        LDA #$00
        STA QUEST_FLAGS,X
        JSR MSG_PRINT
        DC.B "~Ah, ",0
        JSR PRINT_NAME
        JSR MSG_PRINT
        DC.B "!  Thou hast~completed thy quest!~",0
        LDA CASTLE_IDX
        AND #$01
        BNE QUEST_REWARD_HINT
        JSR MSG_PRINT
        DC.B "~For this I will give thee~",0
        LDA #$63
        SEC
        SBC PLR_STR
        LSR
        LSR
        LSR
        BNE .L955E
        LDX PLR_STR
        CPX #$63
        BEQ .L955E
        LDA #$01
.L955E
        STA ZP_T0
        LDX #$00
        STX NUM_PAD
        JSR PRINT_NUM8
        JSR MSG_PRINT
        DC.B " point",0
        LDA ZP_T0
        CMP #$01
        BEQ .L957D
        LDA #$73
        JSR CHAR_OUT
.L957D
        JSR MSG_PRINT
        DC.B " of strength.",0
        LDA PLR_STR
        CLC
        ADC ZP_T0
        STA PLR_STR
        JSR CLEAR_MSGS
        JMP MAP_DRAW
QUEST_REWARD_HINT
        JSR MSG_PRINT
        DC.B "For this I shall tell thee~",0
        LDA PLR_CONT
        ASL
        TAY
        LDA GEM_HINT_TBL,Y
        STA HINT_OP
        LDA GEM_HINT_TBL+1,Y
        STA HINT_OP+1
HINT_OP = *+1
        JSR STALE_FFFF
        JSR CLEAR_MSGS
        JMP MAP_DRAW
@

[[GEM_HINT_TBL]] is the per-continent prophecy table: one handler
address for each of the four continents.

<<cas gem hint table>>=
        ORG $95D6
GEM_HINT_TBL
        DC.W HINT_CONT0
        DC.W HINT_CONT1
        DC.W HINT_CONT2
        DC.W HINT_CONT3
@

\subsection{The gem prophecies}

The four handlers behind [[GEM_HINT_TBL]] spell out Ultima~I's win
condition piece by piece, each handing over a gem ([[OWNED_GEMS]] and
its three successors):

\begin{itemize}
\item [[HINT_CONT0]]: ``all four gems launch a time machine'' --- the
  \emph{red} gem.
\item [[HINT_CONT1]]: ``the time machine must be used to win'' --- the
  \emph{green} gem.
\item [[HINT_CONT2]]: ``the princess will help a space ace through
  time'' --- the \emph{blue} gem.
\item [[HINT_CONT3]]: ``take nine items from my storerooms - but only
  nine'' --- the \emph{white} gem, which also sets [[STORE_PERMIT]]
  to nine.
\end{itemize}

Together with the Princess rescue these are the entire breadcrumb
trail to the endgame: gather four gems from four kings, capture
twenty enemy vessels to become a space ace, rescue the Princess to
reveal the time machine, and use it to travel back and destroy
Mondain's gem.

<<cas gem hints>>=
        ORG $95DE
HINT_CONT0
        SUBROUTINE
