\subsection{Unlock and Ztats}

[[CMD_UNLOCK]] opens a storeroom door with a key dropped by a slain
guard. The faced cell must be a door --- [[$6A]] (silver) or [[$6B]]
(gold) --- and [[KEY_KIND]] must match. The routine builds a pointer
to the door's map row through [[MAP_ROW_LO]]/[[MAP_ROW_HI]],
self-modifies it into [[DOOR_OP]], overwrites the door cell with an
open-floor byte, and redraws. [[CMD_ZTATS]] simply forwards to the
engine [[INVENTORY]] sheet and redraws on return.

<<cas unlock ztats>>=
        ORG $975E
CMD_UNLOCK
        SUBROUTINE
        ; Unlock a storeroom door with a found key; Ztats shows inventory.
        ;
        ; Behavior:
        ;   CMD_UNLOCK: the faced cell must be a door ($6A silver / $6B
        ;   gold) and KEY_KIND must match.  Self-modify the map-row pointer
        ;   DOOR_OP and overwrite the door cell with an open-floor byte,
        ;   then redraw it.  CMD_ZTATS forwards to the engine INVENTORY.
        ;
        ; Clobbers: A, X, Y
        LDX ZP_X
        LDY ZP_Y
        JSR CELL_AT
        CMP #$6A
        BEQ .L9779
        CMP #$6B
        BEQ .L9783
        JSR MSG_PRINT
        DC.B " what",0
        JMP QUERY_MARK
.L9779
        LDA KEY_KIND
        CMP #$01
        BEQ .L97C3
        JMP .L978A
.L9783
        LDA KEY_KIND
        CMP #$02
        BEQ .L97C3
.L978A
        JSR MSG_PRINT
        DC.B "~Thou hast not ",0
        LDA KEY_KIND
        BEQ .L97B4
        JSR MSG_PRINT
        DC.B "the~correct",0
        JMP .L97B9
.L97B4
        LDA #$61
        JSR CHAR_OUT
.L97B9
        JSR MSG_PRINT
        DC.B " key!",0
        RTS
.L97C3
        LDY ZP_Y
        DEY
        LDA MAP_ROW_LO,Y
        CLC
        ADC #$00
        STA DOOR_OP
        LDA MAP_ROW_HI,Y
        ADC #$B4
        STA DOOR_OP+1
        LDX ZP_X
        LDA #$60
DOOR_OP = *+1
        STA STALE_FFFF,X
        JSR MSG_PRINT
        DC.B "~The door is open!",0
        LDX ZP_X
        LDY ZP_Y
        DEY
        LDA #$20
        JMP PLOT_GLYPH
CMD_ZTATS
        JSR INVENTORY
        JMP MAP_DRAW
@

\subsection{The castle tick}

[[CASTLE_TICK]] runs after every command and on every idle timeout
--- the castle's heartbeat, the counterpart of \texttt{TWN}'s town
tick. Its behaviour forks on [[KING_REJECT]]. When the court is calm
it runs [[NPC_WANDER]]: the peaceful inhabitants drift one cell, and
Gwino the Jester ([[WANDER_JESTER]]) either sings ``I've got the
key!'' or filches an unreadied weapon, charisma-gated through
[[PLR_WIS]]. When the King has been angered, [[GUARD_HOME]] homes the
nearest guard on the player using the distance helper [[NPC_DIST]],
and on contact [[GUARD_COMBAT]] strikes --- rolling to hit against
armour and stamina, subtracting damage from [[PLR_HITS]], and routing
a fatal blow to [[CAS_DEATH]] and [[RESPAWN]].

