\subsection{Inform and the map blit}

[[CMD_INFORM]] answers ``where am I'' by naming the place from
[[STR_PLACES]]. [[MAP_DRAW]] --- shared verbatim with \texttt{TWN}
--- swaps the [[MAPCHARS]] glyph bank into the live font through
[[FONT_SWAP]], prints the $38\times18$ cell grid row by row from
[[CASTLE_MAP]] through the engine's glyph output, then overlays each
non-empty NPC slot's glyph from [[NPC_GLYPH]] at its $(x,y)$ and
finally the player marker.

<<cas inform draw>>=
