\subsection{Cell and glyph helpers}

These are the shared low-level helpers, identical in structure to
\texttt{TWN}'s. [[PLOT_GLYPH]] draws a glyph at a cell;
[[CELL_PROBE]] reports whether a cell is passable; [[CELL_AT]] reads
a cell through the [[MAP_ROW_LO]]/[[MAP_ROW_HI]] pointers and, when
the byte is an NPC glyph, scans the sixteen slots to return the NPC's
kind (plus [[$30]]) and stash its slot in [[HIT_SLOT]].
[[RAND_STEP]] and [[RAND_ADJ]] choose a random neighbouring cell for
the wandering NPCs.

