\subsection{Number input}

[[NUM_INPUT]] is the shared decimal entry routine: it accumulates up
to four digits into the 16-bit [[AMOUNT]], multiplying by ten on each
keystroke (an $\times8 + \times2$ shift-add) and supporting backspace
through the undo buffer [[NUM_UNDO]]. The King's pence donation and
the drop-pence handler both read amounts through it.

<<cas num input>>=
        ORG $9C4A
