\subsection{Arithmetic helpers}

The file's last code band holds the math the castle needs.
[[RND_BYTE]] and [[RND_TWO]] feed [[MUL8]], an $8\times8\to16$-bit
shift-and-add multiply used by the storeroom and reward rolls.
[[CLEAR_MSGS]] restores the map window and waits for a key.
[[NPC_DIST]] returns the distance from the player to a given NPC slot
--- $dx^2 + dy^2$ followed by an inline integer square root, the same
kernel the dungeon and town use for homing --- and [[GUARD_HOME]]
uses it to steer guards. [[ADD_CAP]] is the capped adder behind the
Princess rescue: it adds a 16-bit value with the $+500$ bonus folded
in and clamps the total at 9999.

<<cas math helpers>>=
        ORG $9CF1
RND_BYTE
        SUBROUTINE
        ; Random-byte helpers, MUL8, CLEAR_MSGS, NPC_DIST, ADD_CAP.
        ;
        ; Behavior:
        ;   RND_BYTE/RND_TWO seed the bit-multiply MUL8 (an 8x8 -> 16-bit
        ;   shift-and-add).  CLEAR_MSGS restores the map window and waits.
        ;   NPC_DIST returns the integer distance from the player to NPC
        ;   slot X (dx^2 + dy^2 then an inline square root).  ADD_CAP adds
        ;   A:X with the +500 reward and clamps the result at 9999.
        ;
        ; Clobbers: A, X, Y
        JSR RND
.L9CF4
        STA ZP_T0
        STA MUL_MASK
        JMP MUL8
RND_TWO
        JSR RND
        PHA
        JSR .L9CF4
        STA ZP_T0
        PLA
        STA MUL_MASK
        JMP MUL8
MUL8
        LDA #$00
        STA ZP_T1
        STA MUL_ACC
        STA MUL_ACC+1
        LDX #$07
.L9D18
        LDA MUL_MASK
        AND #$01
        BNE .L9D30
        LDA MUL_ACC
        CLC
        ADC ZP_T0
        STA MUL_ACC
        LDA MUL_ACC+1
        ADC ZP_T1
