\subsection{The enemy ship sprites}

The enemy craft is stored as a sprite atlas at the file tail: nine
distance scales (a single dot at the farthest range growing to a
three-column, forty-five-row craft at point-blank) followed by
twenty-seven rotation frames. Six parallel 36-entry tables describe each
shape: [[SHAPE_PTR_LO]]/[[SHAPE_PTR_HI]] give the pixel pointer,
[[SHAPE_WID]]/[[SHAPE_HGT]] the dimensions in 7-pixel columns and rows,
and [[SHAPE_XOFF]]/[[SHAPE_YOFF]] the centring offsets (which double as
the firing hit box). [[SHAPE_PIXELS]] holds the packed hi-res bytes. The
blitter ([[BLIT_SHAPE_AT]]) pre-shifts a shape into byte alignment and
XOR-draws it, so the same routine both draws and erases.
Figure~\ref{fig:spa-ships} shows the nine distance scales of the enemy
craft, and Figure~\ref{fig:spa-shapes-all} the full atlas including its
rotation frames.

