\subsection{The disk formatter}

Everything from here serves one goal: take a blank or foreign disk and turn it
into an empty \texttt{/U1.PLAYER} ProDOS volume the game can save to. It is a
self-contained subsystem; nothing in normal play reaches it.

The front end picks a slot and drive, defaulting to the ProDOS last-used
device. Digit keys edit the fields (slot 1--7, drive 1--2), return accepts,
escape backs out, and \texttt{MLIB\_ONLINE} refuses a slot/drive with no
disk in it.

<<gen format entry>>=
        ORG $90D7
FORMAT_ENTRY
        SUBROUTINE
        ; Disk formatter front end: choose the slot and drive.
        ;
        ; Behavior:
        ;   FORMAT_ENTRY derives a default slot/drive from the ProDOS last-used
        ;   device number (PRODOS_DEVNUM).  FORMAT_RESTART draws "Slot: ( )" /
        ;   "Drive: ( )" and runs SLOT_KEYLOOP / DRIVE_KEYLOOP: digits update
        ;   the field (slot 1..7, drive 1..2), return accepts, escape aborts.
        ;   MLIB_ONLINE rejects a slot/drive with no disk.  When both are set,
        ;   control passes to VOL_CHECK.
        ;
        ; Clobbers: A, X, Y
        LDA PRODOS_DEVNUM
        TAX
        AND #$80
        ASL
        ROL
        ADC #$01
        STA ZP_DRIVE
        TXA
        LSR
        LSR
        LSR
        LSR
        AND #$07
        STA ZP_SLOT
FORMAT_RESTART
        JSR WINFULL_HOME
        JSR PROMPT_LINE
        DC.B "Enter the Slot & Drive numbers~ for the new player disk.",0
        LDX #$09
        LDY #$09
        JSR MSG_AT
        DC.B "Slot: ( )",0
        LDX #$08
        LDY #$0B
        JSR MSG_AT
        DC.B "Drive: ( )",0
        LDA #$10
        STA MON_CH
        LDA #$09
        STA MON_CV
        LDA ZP_SLOT
        JSR PRINT_DIGIT
        LDA #$10
        STA MON_CH
        LDA #$0B
        STA MON_CV
        LDA ZP_DRIVE
        JSR PRINT_DIGIT
        LDA #$13
        STA MON_CH
        LDA #$09
        STA MON_CV
SLOT_KEYLOOP
        JSR KEY_WAIT
        CMP #$0D
        BEQ .L9182
        SEC
        SBC #$30
        BEQ .L9192
        CMP #$08
        BCS .L9192
        STA ZP_SLOT
.L9182
        LDA #$13
        STA MON_CH
        LDA #$09
        STA MON_CV
        LDA ZP_SLOT
        JSR PRINT_DIGIT
        JMP .L9197
.L9192
        JSR MLIB_ONLINE
        BEQ SLOT_KEYLOOP
.L9197
        LDA #$13
        STA MON_CH
        LDA #$0B
        STA MON_CV
DRIVE_KEYLOOP
        JSR KEY_WAIT
        CMP #$1B
        BNE .L91A7
        RTS
.L91A7
        CMP #$0D
        BEQ .L91B6
        SEC
        SBC #$30
        BEQ .L91C6
        CMP #$03
        BCS .L91C6
        STA ZP_DRIVE
.L91B6
        LDA #$13
        STA MON_CH
        LDA #$0B
        STA MON_CV
        LDA ZP_DRIVE
        JSR PRINT_DIGIT
        JMP VOL_CHECK
.L91C6
        JSR MLIB_ONLINE
        BEQ DRIVE_KEYLOOP
@ %def FORMAT_ENTRY FORMAT_RESTART SLOT_KEYLOOP DRIVE_KEYLOOP

With a target chosen, \texttt{VOL\_CHECK} confirms it is a Disk~II (other
device types are rejected), asks ProDOS whether the disk is already a known
volume so it can warn before overwriting, and requires an explicit ``Y'' to
proceed. \texttt{DO\_FORMAT} then brackets the destructive work by saving and
restoring the engine's zero-page scratch, calling first the low-level
\texttt{RWTS\_FORMAT} to write the magnetic format and then
\texttt{FORMAT\_VOLUME} to lay down the directory.

<<gen vol check>>=
        ORG $91CB
VOL_CHECK
        SUBROUTINE
        ; Verify the target disk, confirm, and dispatch the format.
        ;
        ; Behavior:
        ;   VOL_CHECK reads the device's boot block and tests for a Disk II
        ;   ($Cn ROM signature); NO_DISKII rejects other devices.  TEST_ONLINE
        ;   asks ProDOS whether the disk is already a known volume and, if so,
        ;   shows its name; NON_PRODOS handles an unformatted disk.  CONFIRM_FMT
        ;   prints "...? (Y-N)" and waits for Y.  DO_FORMAT saves the zero-page
        ;   scratch, calls the low-level RWTS_FORMAT, then the volume-directory
        ;   writer, restoring zero page around the call.
        ;
        ; Clobbers: A, X, Y
        JSR CLEAR_FROM20
        LDA #$00
        STA ZP_BLK_PTR
        LDA ZP_SLOT
        ORA #$C0
        STA ZP_BLK_PTR+1
        LDY #$01
        LDA (ZP_BLK_PTR),Y
        CMP #$20
        BNE NO_DISKII
        LDY #$03
        LDA (ZP_BLK_PTR),Y
        BNE NO_DISKII
        LDY #$05
        LDA (ZP_BLK_PTR),Y
        CMP #$03
        BNE NO_DISKII
        LDY #$FF
        LDA (ZP_BLK_PTR),Y
        BNE NO_DISKII
        LDA ZP_SLOT
        ASL
        LDX ZP_DRIVE
        CPX #$02
        BNE .L9200
        CLC
        ADC #$10
.L9200
        TAX
        LDA PRODOS_DEVTAB,X
        CMP PRODOS_DEVTAB
        BNE TEST_ONLINE
        LDA $BF11,X
        CMP $BF11
