\texttt{RW\_WRITE\_DELAY} writes one nibble and burns the exact cycles a
4-microsecond bit cell needs, so the bitstream lands at the right density ---
the timing is the format.

<<gen rwts delay>>=
        ORG $AB3A
RW_WRITE_DELAY
        SUBROUTINE
        ; Timed nibble write (motor pacing).
        ;
        ; Behavior:
        ;   Write the nibble in A to the drive's data latch and burn the exact
        ;   number of cycles a 4us nibble cell requires, so the bitstream is
        ;   laid down at the correct density.
        ;
        ; Clobbers: A
        LDX #$11
.LAB3C
        DEX
        BNE .LAB3C
        INC RW_T9
        BNE .LAB45
        INC RW_TA
.LAB45
        SEC
        SBC #$01
        BNE RW_WRITE_DELAY
        RTS
@ %def RW_WRITE_DELAY

