\subsection{Entering the craft}

[[TM_ENTRY]] is where the loader lands. It arms the boss fight --- seeding
[[GEM_HP]] to $1000$ and clearing [[CUR_MON]] --- draws the craft interior, and
runs the framed intro narration that establishes the four gem sockets and the
\textsc{launch} button.

<<tm entry>>=
        ORG $8AD7
TM_ENTRY
        SUBROUTINE
        ; Endgame entry: arm Mondain's gem, draw the craft, run the intro.
        ;
        ; Behavior:
        ;   Set GEM_HP <- #$03E8 (1000 = the gem-of-immortality hit points that
        ;   gate Mondain's life) and CUR_MON <- #$00.  Build the interior scene
        ;   (the .L9E95 / .L9E50 / .L9E6C renderer setup), print the framed
        ;   intro narration ("Entering the craft... four holes marked R G B W
        ;   ... a button marked LAUNCH ... press it!"), and draw the four
        ;   colored gem-socket markers at x = $5E/$73/$88/$9D in colors
        ;   5/1/6/7 (R/G/B/W) via the LA44B socket drawer.
        ;
        ; Modifies:
        ;   GEM_HP, CUR_MON
        ; Clobbers: A, X, Y
        LDX #$E8
        LDA #$03
        STX GEM_HP
        STA GEM_HP+1
        LDA #$00
        STA CUR_MON
        LDA #$00
        JSR SETUP_SHAPE
        JSR SCENE_CLEAR
        LDA #$00
        LDY #$FF
        JSR PLACE_SHAPE
        JSR POPUP_TEXT_NF
        DC.B "|",$7F,$03,"Entering the craft, thou dost|",$7F,$03,"remark upon four holes marked:|||",$7F,$0D,"R  G  B  W|| The proper gems fit in each hole.||",$7F,$05,"Further examination leads|",$7F,$06,"thee to two discoveries:||",$7F,$02,"There is a button marked LAUNCH,|",$7F,$04,"and thou art locked in, with|",$7F,$04,"nothing to do but press it!",0
        LDX #$5E
        LDA #$05
        JSR DRAW_SOCKET
        LDX #$73
        LDA #$01
        JSR DRAW_SOCKET
        LDX #$88
        LDA #$06
        JSR DRAW_SOCKET
        LDX #$9D
        LDA #$07
        JSR DRAW_SOCKET
        JSR POPUP_REDRAW
@ %def TM_ENTRY

The launch sequence is pure narration: three framed panels carry the player
from pressing the black \textsc{launch} button, through the journey ``through
time,'' to coming ``face to face with the evil Mondain himself.'' Each panel is
a \texttt{POPUP\_TEXT\_NF} call followed by [[POPUP_REDRAW]] and an
[[MON_CV]] bump to step down the screen.

<<tm launch>>=
        ORG $8C25
        INC MON_CV
        JSR POPUP_TEXT_NF
        DC.B "|||  As soon as thou hast pressed the|large black button, lights begin to| dance across the control screens.||",$7F,$02,"Generators shake the very floor|",$7F,$09,"beneath thy feet.|| The small craft begins to tremble|",$7F,$05,"and rattle as thy journey|",$7F,$07,"through time begins...",0
        JSR POPUP_REDRAW
        INC MON_CV
        JSR POPUP_TEXT_NF
        DC.B "|||||| After but a few moments thou dost| feel a strong magic pulling thee|",$7F,$09,"from thy craft...",0
        JSR POPUP_REDRAW
        INC MON_CV
        JSR POPUP_TEXT_NF
        DC.B "||||",$7F,$09,"...A moment later,|",$7F,$07,"thou art face to face|",$7F,$03,"with the evil Mondain himself!||||",$7F,$07,"Good luck, this is it!",0
        JSR POPUP_REDRAW
@

With the narration done, the scene is built: Mondain and the Gem are placed as
cells on the small interior grid (their positions cached in
