@ %def TM_ATTACK HIT_RESOLVE TM_VICTORY PICK_DIR STR_RESTART

\subsection{Spells}

[[TM_CAST]] mirrors the attack path for magic: it validates the readied spell
against [[OWNED_SPELLS]] and dispatches through [[TM_SPELL_TBL]] via another
self-modified jump ([[SPELL_JMP]]).

<<tm cast>>=
        ORG $91FB
TM_CAST
        SUBROUTINE
        ; CAST command: dispatch the readied spell.
        ;
        ; Behavior:
        ;   Print the spell name (PRINT_SPELL), refuse a used-up spell
        ;   ("Thou hast used up that spell!" via OWNED_SPELLS), then index
        ;   TM_SPELL_TBL by 2*READY_SPELL and copy the handler address over the
        ;   self-modified JMP operand (SPELL_JMP) before jumping to it.
        ;
        ; Modifies:
        ;   SPELL_JMP (self-modified jump target), CUR_MON
        ; Clobbers: A, X, Y
        JSR PRINT_SPELL
        LDX READY_SPELL
        BEQ .L922D
        LDA OWNED_SPELLS,X
        BNE .L922D
        JSR MSG_PRINT
        DC.B "~Thou hast used up that spell!",0
        JMP BEEP_CMD
.L922D
        LDA CUR_MON
        BNE .L9235
        INC CUR_MON
.L9235
        LDA READY_SPELL
        ASL
        TAY
        LDA TM_SPELL_TBL,Y
        STA SPELL_JMP
        LDA TM_SPELL_TBL+1,Y
        STA SPELL_JMP+1
SPELL_JMP = *+1
        JMP SPELL_PRAYER
@ %def TM_CAST

[[TM_SPELL_TBL]] holds the eleven spell-handler addresses indexed by
[[READY_SPELL]]; most point at the not-applicable tail, with magic missile and
a handful of grid effects being the spells that actually do something here.

<<tm spell tbl>>=
        ORG $9249
TM_SPELL_TBL
        HEX ce92b792b792d992
        HEX b792b792b7924a93
        HEX 9293e8937594
@ %def TM_SPELL_TBL

<<tm spell helpers>>=
        ORG $925F
CAST_CHECK
        SUBROUTINE
        ; Cast-success check and the shared failure / not-applicable tails.
        ;
        ; Behavior:
        ;   .L925F consumes one charge of the readied spell (OWNED_SPELLS),
        ;   then decides success: a Cleric (PLR_CLASS = 2) auto-passes, others
        ;   roll against RND; range is gated through .L9D5C and PLR_INT is
        ;   rolled against RND.  Carry clear = success, set = failure.  .L929F
        ;   prints " failed!" and beeps; the fall-through entries print
        ;   "Not applicable!" / route to NO_EFFECT_MSG for the inert spells.
        ;
        ; Outputs:
        ;   Carry clear on success, set on failure.
        ; Clobbers: A, X, Y
        LDX READY_SPELL
        BEQ .L9267
        DEC OWNED_SPELLS,X
.L9267
        LDA PLR_CLASS
        CMP #$02
        BEQ .L9275
        LDA #$03
        JSR RND_MOD
        BEQ .L929D
.L9275
        LDA READY_SPELL
        CMP #$08
        BEQ .L9287
        CMP #$09
        BEQ .L9287
        JSR CELL_DISTANCE
        CMP #$07
        BCS .L929D
.L9287
        LDA #$0A
        JSR SFX_PLAY
        LDA PLR_INT
        CLC
        ADC #$80
        STA ZP_C3
        JSR RND
        CMP ZP_C3
        BCS .L929D
        CLC
        RTS
.L929D
        SEC
        RTS
SPELL_FAILED
        LDA MON_CH
        CMP #$16
        BCC .L92A8
        JSR NEWLINE
.L92A8
        JSR MSG_PRINT
        DC.B " failed!",0
        JMP BEEP_CMD
        JSR MSG_PRINT
        DC.B "~Not applicable!",0
        JMP BEEP_CMD
SPELL_PRAYER
        JSR CAST_CHECK
        BCC .L92D6
        JMP SPELL_FAILED
.L92D6
        JMP NO_EFFECT_MSG
@ %def CAST_CHECK SPELL_FAILED SPELL_PRAYER

The one offensive spell that matters against the gem is magic missile: it rolls
damage from [[PLR_INT]], scales it by the readied weapon class, and feeds the
result into the same hit-resolution code [[TM_ATTACK]] uses.

<<tm spell missile>>=
        ORG $92D9
        JSR MSG_PRINT
        DC.B ": ",0
        JSR PICK_DIR
        BNE .L92ED
        JSR MSG_PRINT
        DC.B "pass",0
        RTS
.L92ED
        SUBROUTINE
        ; Magic-missile spell aimed at Mondain.
        ;
        ; Behavior:
        ;   Prompt for a direction (.L916F); on a valid cast (.L925F) and a
        ;   facing of Mondain, roll base damage from PLR_INT and scale it by
        ;   the readied weapon class (8 -> 1.5x, 9 -> 2x, 10..11 -> 3x), store
        ;   DMG_AMT, then jump into the shared hit-resolution path (.L8F80,
        ;   the "Hit Mondain!" / GEM_HP-drain code).
        ;
        ; Modifies:
        ;   DMG_AMT
        ; Clobbers: A, X, Y
        TXA
        PHA
        JSR CAST_CHECK
        BCC .L92F8
        PLA
        JMP SPELL_FAILED
.L92F8
        PLA
        CMP #$02
        BEQ .L930A
        JSR MSG_PRINT
        DC.B "~Missed!",0
        RTS
.L930A
        LDA PLR_INT
        JSR RND_MOD
        BNE .L9314
        LDA #$01
.L9314
        STA DMG_AMT
        LDA READY_WEAPON
        CMP #$08
        BNE .L9329
        LDA DMG_AMT
        LSR
        CLC
        ADC DMG_AMT
        JMP .L9344
.L9329
        CMP #$09
        BNE .L9334
        LDA DMG_AMT
        ASL
        JMP .L9344
.L9334
        CMP #$0A
        BCC .L9347
        CMP #$0C
        BCS .L9347
        LDA DMG_AMT
        ASL
        CLC
        ADC DMG_AMT
.L9344
        STA DMG_AMT
.L9347
        JMP HIT_RESOLVE
