[[MONDAIN_TURN]] is the wizard's AI. It chooses an action by distance to the
player: adjacent he attacks in melee, at middle range he may cast, and far away
he steps toward the player. His gem regenerates as he acts, healing [[GEM_HP]]
back toward $500$ and cycling his sprite state --- which is why the player must
keep up the pressure once the gem is destroyed.
Figure~\ref{fig:mondain-ai} states the AI as the three-way distance choice
plus the gem-regeneration side effect that makes him so dangerous while the
Gem of Immortality still stands.

\begin{figure}[ht]
\centering
\begin{tikzpicture}[dg, >=Stealth, node distance=7mm and 13mm]
  \node[dgterminal] (e) {MONDAIN\_TURN};
  \node[dgdecision, below=of e] (dist) {distance to\\player?};
  \node[dgprocess, below=of dist] (mid) {mid range};
  \node[dgprocess, left=16mm of dist] (adj) {adjacent};
  \node[dgprocess, right=16mm of dist] (far) {far};
  \node[dgprocess, below=of adj] (melee) {MONDAIN\_MELEE\\\scriptsize strike player};
  \node[dgdecision, below=of mid] (roll) {1/2 roll?};
  \node[dgprocess, below=of roll] (cast)
        {MONDAIN\_CAST\\\scriptsize one of 3 spells};
  \node[dgnote, right=2mm of cast] {missile / mind blast /\\psionic shock};
  \node[dgprocess, below=of far] (step)
        {MONDAIN\_STEP\\\scriptsize biased wander toward player};
  % the gem-regen side effect
  \node[dgprocess, dgaccentnode, below=22mm of cast, text width=34mm]
        (regen) {while gem stands: GEM\_HP += 5 toward 500; cycle sprite state};

  \draw[->] (e)--(dist);
  \draw[->] (dist) -- node[dgnote,above]{adjacent} (adj);
  \draw[->] (dist) -- node[dgnote,left]{mid} (mid);
  \draw[->] (dist) -- node[dgnote,above]{far} (far);
  \draw[->] (adj)--(melee);
  \draw[->] (mid)--(roll);
  \draw[->] (roll) -- node[dgnote,left]{yes} (cast);
  \draw[->] (roll.east) -- node[dgnote,above]{no} ($(roll.east)+(8mm,0)$) |- (step.north east);
  \draw[->] (far)--(step);
  % all actions feed the regen tick
  \draw[->, dgaccentedge] (melee) |- (regen.west);
  \draw[->, dgaccentedge] (cast) -- (regen);
  \draw[->, dgaccentedge] (step) |- (regen.east);
\end{tikzpicture}
\caption{Mondain's AI ([[MONDAIN_TURN]]): a three-way choice on distance
  --- melee when adjacent, a coin-flip cast (one of three spells) at mid
  range, a biased step toward the player when far. Every action also runs
  the highlighted gem regeneration: while the Gem of Immortality stands,
  [[GEM_HP]] heals five per turn toward 500, so the player must destroy the
  gem ([[TM_GET]]) and then finish him before it recovers.}
\label{fig:mondain-ai}
\end{figure}

